-- Aston Villa Defeats Norwich 1-0 in English Premier League Soccer
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2013-09-21T14:01:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-09-21/aston-villa-defeats-norwich-1-0-in-english-premier-league-soccer.html
Brad Guzan saved a penalty kick to
help Aston Villa defeat Norwich 1-0 in English soccer’s Premier
League.  Guzan stopped Robert Snodgrass’s penalty in the first half
and also made a lunging one-handed save against  Gary Hooper  with
two minutes remaining at Carrow Road in Norwich.  Libor Kozak scored in the 30th minute after replacing
Villa’s top scorer Christian Benteke, who left with an injury.  Villa ended a run of 26 straight games allowing a goal, the
longest current streak in the Premier League.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  